name: Austin Community College: Highland Business Center
directions: Third floor, take a sharp right if you're coming out of the elevators. If you're heading to the elevators, the restroom is on your left.
comment: ACC has a diverse student population, which makes it fairly easy to get up to this floor. If you don't have a parking permit, across the street there's a hotel you can park at and there is also the mall parking open, too. Not sure how/if these other areas are monitored. The stall is large and the main entrance to the restroom can be locked.

name: Brown BioMed
directions: 3rd floor on the side of the building near Brown St (Grimshaw wing)

name: Starbucks
directions: Both bathrooms by the front door are marked gender neutral

name: Square du 8 Mai 1945
directions: Opposite Boulevard Alexandre III
comment: Costs 0,50€. Open Mon-Sun 8am-9pm.

name: Promenade de la Pantiero
directions: In a poster fixture next to a newspaper stand
comment: Costs 0,50€. Open Mon-Sun 8am-9pm.

name: Rofla Rastplatz
directions: Only accessible for those going northbound on the highway (direction of Chur)

name: Le Kashmir Indian Restaurant
directions: Inside the restaurant at the back on the right hand side.
comment: Sadly for customers of the restaurant only (which is very good and staff is quite nice).

name: Paulie's
directions: Directly to the left of the front door
comment: Usually only for customers; it's a restaurant

name: Juliette Gordon Low Birthplace
directions: It's in the room you wait for the tour in.

name: Patisserie Valerie
directions: When you enter just turn left, you'll see the bathroom rightaway.
comment: You have to be a paying customer tho. Try to blend in with the others or simply buy something (although their food isn't really good)

name: Bluebeard Gastropub
directions: In the bar area
comment: Customers only

name: Crown Hill Funeral Home
directions: Not located near the gendered bathrooms. Directly to the right of the main entrance.

name: Macy's Second Floor
directions: Family bathroom by the mattresses and travel suitcases, right by the escalator.

name: Universeum
comment: For paying customers.

name: LeVeque Tower
directions: Go in Front St entrance; bathroom is to the left, kind of tucked away

name: Target
directions: Accessible Family Restroom at entrance. Enter store and immediately turn left.

name: Devonshire Mall
directions: Bathrooms are near the food court
comment: The main mall bathrooms are free to use for anyone, and there is a family restroom. There is also a single stall gender neutral bathroom in the movie theatre but you have to have a ticket to access it.

name: Ikea
directions: first floor up the escalator
comment: two family restrooms

name: Wegmans
directions: From the left entrance, head up the stairs to the second level of the cafe. Head down the hallway to the right of the elevators, it will be on the left.
comment: It's pretty secluded when it's not around meal times, so there shouldn't be too many people. It's one room with a lockable door.

name: Northwest dental
directions: To the right of the front door. Single stall. non-gendered.
comment: For customers of NW Dental

name: Bryant Lake Bowl
directions: In the theater. Go from the bar into the bowling alley, then take a left through the double doors. It will be in the back of the theater.

name: Enloe Prompt Cal Park
directions: ask reception, then follow the signs down the hall. there are two bathrooms.
comment: there are also two vending machines there. the drink one takes card, but the snack one is cash only.

name: Publix Supermarket
directions: Through front doors, take a right, next to flowers.
comment: Single use family restroom behind gendered restrooms.

name: Resendiz family fruit barn
directions: On the side if the building near park
comment: May or may not need a key to get in

name: Reeves Center
comment: There is a security check to get in, but as this building houses the DC Center for the LGBT Community and the Mayor's Office on LGBT Affairs, security is usually good. These are all-gender, multi stall restrooms.

name: Costa Coffee
directions: At the back on the left (there's a sign on the wall).
comment: Two unisex stalls, one accessible.

name: Sam's Club
directions:
Family bathroom in between gender bathrooms
Front part of store along the side wall past the eatery.
comment: No membership needed to enter warehouse, only if purchasing items.

name: Bob Evans
directions: You just go to where the sign says restrooms, and it will say "family restroom" AKA gender neutral bathroom
comment: if you are not eating here, you can just walk by, and if anyone asks just say you are using the restroom.

name: La Fiesta Restaurant
directions: All the way in the back corner (in the farthest dining area)

name: Starbucks
directions: back of the store/side entrance
comment: you need to ask baristas for the code, the sign on the door says customers only, but in my experience they don't care

name: New York eater Gotham west market
Target
directions: By the pharmacy

name: Royal Cinema
directions: Upstairs
comment: Gender- neutral multistall bathroom - 4 stalls and 2 sinks in one room.

name: Chickadee Cottage Cafe
comment: You have to be a paying customer or just browse over their gift shop for a bit

name: The Americana Company Antiques
directions: When you enter the stoor turn left and walk all the way to the last passage. Then, go straight untill the wall. The bathroom will be on the right. The door does not say bathroom, but it does have a note on it that says to knock.

name: Zada James Corner Cafe
directions: When you enter go left and make a u turn. There are single stall gendered restrooms.
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Hollis Social Library
directions: As you enter the building, it's right on the left. Two single room bathrooms, no specified gender for either.
comment: You do not need to be a library member or anything to be able to acces the bathrooms.

name: AmericInn
directions: Upon entering hotel turn left at the front desk and it will be on the right before you get to the hotel rooms

name: Lakeview Campgrounds
directions: Pull in main gate drive ahead untill you see a white building with 2 doors go in door on right bathroom is just down a short hall on right is also ADA compliant
comment: This is a great place to stay very clean and owned by nice people all friendly to the LGBT community

name: SuperValu
comment: You have to ask for the key at the tills.

name: Killington Grand Hotel
directions: Second floor. If you go up the stairs to the left of the main entrance and through the door onto the second floor, it's straight ahead. If you use the elevator, that's also to the left of the main entrance but around a corner, it's to the right.
comment: You don't have to be a guest. If you're not sure how to find it, ask at the front desk where there's a single stall bathroom. They'll direct you upstairs. If they do ask what you're doing there, tell them you wanted to check out Preston's restaurant.

name: The Portland Loo
directions: Center of Mass Ave across from Old Burying Ground
comment: Outdoor free public toilet

name: Pet Alliance of Greater Orlando (Sanford Location)
directions: Inside Adoption Lobby. Also inside Dog Lobby

name: Target
directions: Towards the back on the left

name: Coupeville Wharf
directions: Enter the red building that says "Coupeville" and go to the second room on your right.

name: Loretta's Northwestner
directions: Straight inside on the right, after the booths

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back of the store
comment: Must be paying customer

name: Opry Mills Mall Food Court
directions: Back of the food court, next to Chili's and Charlie's- there's a waiting area with the changing table, then a separate room for nursing and a restroom.
comment: Just go right in the first door.

name: Ciao Italian Restaurant
directions: It's on the second floor. Go up the stairs inside the building and turn around the quarter to your right. Or, go up the outdoor stairs and turn to your left. You will see two gender-neutral individual restrooms.

name: Kaiser Permanente
directions: Enter any building; there are several.
comment: Very plentiful amount of bathrooms.

name: Jiffy Lube
comment: Garage/car wash. No urinal.

name: Cold Spot for Healthy Pets
directions: One by the from door and one by the travel section.

name: Natural Bridge State Park
directions: Inside the gift shop, toward the park entrance.

name: James Baird State Park
directions: It's on the ground floor to the right of the entrance.
comment: It didn't have a rail but the toilet was low and wide.

name: Brevard Music Center
directions: Go to the stables building (houses the student services and mailboxes). In the porch around the garden there are 2 gendered bathrooms and one that is unmarked so everyone uses it.

name: Peeled Juice Bar
directions: At the back. It has no steps, but you do have to navigate past tightly packed tables and chairs, so may not be accessible to all.
comment: I think you have to be a paying customer. Also, door doesn't appear to have a lock, which is a safety concern.

name: Starbucks
directions: When you walk in the door, walk straight forward until you see an opening to your right, there should be two single-stall bathrooms

name: Black Crow on Main
directions: From the front door, go down the aisle to your right, both are just past the stairwell to the basement.
comment: Wonderful antiques & vintage items, highly recommend exploring. Haven't tried their café yet.

name: Magic City Acceptance Center
directions: Turn right, and it's the first door on your left.

name: Oregon zoo
directions: Near elephant pool and stadium

name: Recycled Books and Records
directions: on the ground floor through the childrens book section

name: Marymoor Park, near Velodrone
street: near 6046 West Lake Sammamish Pkwy NE
directions: Near the velodrome in Marymoor Park
comment: Three single stall restrooms, one accessible.

name: Starbucks
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Starbucks
street: The Tower Guoman Hotel, St Katharine's Way
directions: On your right as you walk in. On the ground floor

name: Upper Anderson (Anderson Auditorium, second floor)
directions:
*NOTE: this address is incorrect. cannot find the address of the auditorium itself. sorry for inconvenience*
facing the main entrance, walk in and go up the stairwell on the right-hand side (or use the elevator).

name: Upper Anderson (second floor, Anderson Auditorium)
directions: if you're facing the front entrance of the building, go up the set of staircases on the right. an elevator is also there, so it is accessible. there are 3 gender neutral restrooms at the top of the stairs.

name: 7-Eleven
directions: Through the double doors, all the way to the right.

name: Sushi Deli 1
directions: Enter and go around to the back.
comment: Because of long wait times to be seated, you could easily get in.

name: Haymarket Café
directions: One upstairs, two downstairs. All of them have no gender marker. They're unisex.
comment: The toilet upstairs is wheelchair accessible but the ones downstairs might be harder to get to. They now have you ask for a key before using the toilets for safety reasons but you don't have to be a paying customer. Really amazing queer-friendly place for all people :-) ALL people.

name: Bruegger's Bagels
directions: In the restaurant. It's downstairs near their kitchens.
comment: I have no experience being a non-paying customer and using it but I'm assuming you can.

name: Mt. Tom's Homemade Ice Cream
directions: In the back of the ice cream parlor to the right.
comment: Everybody there is kind and trans-friendly. You can get free water there and you don't have to pay. The toilet is open to anybody, just rather small.

name: Huntington Bank
directions: When you walk in the front door, go into the hallway to the left of the counter

name: Nacho Mamas
directions: Back of restaurant
comment: Nice people

name: Burton Hall
directions: Up the stairs and to your left.
comment: It gets extremely minimal traffic and is always spacious and clean.

name: Plum Blossom Tea Company
directions: Unmarked door across from Heart of Zen entrance, next to the Plum Blossom Tea inside entrance.
comment: Ask anyone in the tea shop and they can assist you <3

name: Lucky Beach
directions: Up the stairs
